<div id="review_402499690" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/402499690" />
    <a title="Samira" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11171429-samira"><img alt="Samira" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/402499690?book_show_action=true">Aug 28, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Samira" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Samira" href="/user/show/11171429-samira">Samira</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11171429-samira?shelf=historical">historical</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer402499690" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2122416011282730359">Really interesting book about Polish history spanning centuries. Makes you in turn marvel at the stupidity of the Polish magnates, shake your head at strange occurrences and wonder why you never heard about such important events in European history before. Educating and informative read.<br/><br/>It also has a rather good introduction explaining exactly what is historically accurate and what part is fiction. Very good and obviously well-researched book.<br/><br/>However, one should have a fairly good knowledge abou</span>
  <span id="freeText2122416011282730359" style="display:none">Really interesting book about Polish history spanning centuries. Makes you in turn marvel at the stupidity of the Polish magnates, shake your head at strange occurrences and wonder why you never heard about such important events in European history before. Educating and informative read.<br /><br />It also has a rather good introduction explaining exactly what is historically accurate and what part is fiction. Very good and obviously well-researched book.<br /><br />However, one should have a fairly good knowledge about European history in general beforehand. The larger context is not explained, it is assumed that the reader knows about the happenings in other countries at the respective time.<br /><br />Also western-style capitalist democracy is markedly favoured when compared to any of the other possibilities explored throughout Polish history. This often comes across as preaching a doctrine more than stating a logical and well-founded opinion. It makes the book seem heavily biased and containing a US-American point of view rather than the objective historical account it otherwise tries to be.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2122416011282730359" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


